  <sect2 role="installation">
    <title>Installation of libarchive</title>

    <para>
      Install <application>libarchive</application> by running the following
      commands:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>./configure --prefix=/usr --disable-static &amp;&amp;
make</userinput></screen>

    <!-- non-root: https://github.com/libarchive/libarchive/issues/2995 -->
    <para>
      To test the results, issue: <command>make check</command>
      as a non-&root; user.
    </para>

    <para>
      Now, as the <systemitem class="username">root</systemitem> user:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>make install</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Still as the &root; user, create a symlink so we can use
      <command>bsdunzip</command> as <command>unzip</command>, instead
      of relying on the unmaintained Unzip package:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>ln -sfv bsdunzip /usr/bin/unzip</userinput></screen>

    <note>
      <para>
        As discussed in <xref linkend='locale-wrong-filename-encoding'/>,
        if the Zip archive to be extracted contains any file with a name
        containing any non-Latin characters, you need to manually specify
        the encoding of those characters or they will be turned into
        unreadable sequences in the extracted file name.  For example, if a
        Zip archive created with WinZip, <filename>archive.zip</filename>,
        contains a file named with Simplified Chinese characters, the
        encoding should be CP936 and the <parameter>-I cp936</parameter>
        option should be used.  I.e. the command to extract the archive
        should be <command>unzip -I cp936 archive.zip</command>.
      </para>
    </note>

  </sect2>

  <sect2 role="commands">
    <title>Command Explanations</title>

    <xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
      href="../../xincludes/static-libraries.xml"/>

    <para>
      <option>--without-xml2</option>: This switch uses expat for xar archive
      format support instead of libxml2 (which is preferred) if both packages
      are installed.
    </para>

    <para>
      <option>--with-nettle</option>: This switch uses Nettle for crypto
      support instead of OpenSSL. This support is known to be broken upstream
      due to Nettle-4.0.
      <!-- Originally I reverted the commit where I added this because I had
      a patch from upstream. The patch turned out to be insufficient, it fixes
      the compiler errors but then generates numerous amounts of undefined
      reference errors at link time. I chimed in on the upstream bug report
      at https://github.com/libarchive/libarchive/issues/2876 - and the PR
      I used to try fixing it was:
      https://github.com/libarchive/libarchive/pull/2858
      Since this support is explicitly opt-in, let's just note it's broken
      for now and I will follow up when upstream gets back to me. -renodr
      -->
    </para>

  </sect2>

